1
00:01:14,480 --> 00:01:19,164
<i>[Meet Yourself]</i>

2
00:01:19,164 --> 00:01:23,600
<i>[Episode 26]</i>

3
00:01:32,120 --> 00:01:34,260
Look at this. It's Aunty E's dried fish.

4
00:01:34,260 --> 00:01:35,640
- They're really well dried.
- Yes.

5
00:01:35,640 --> 00:01:37,660
Better than mine.

6
00:01:40,400 --> 00:01:42,900
What's she doing?

7
00:01:42,900 --> 00:01:45,511
No clue. Is she exercising?

8
00:01:46,400 --> 00:01:48,092
Doesn't she feel dizzy?

9
00:01:48,092 --> 00:01:49,450
I don't know.

10
00:01:49,450 --> 00:01:50,760
Look.

11
00:01:50,760 --> 00:01:52,260
Check out her waist.

12
00:01:52,260 --> 00:01:53,410
Look at it.

13
00:01:53,410 --> 00:01:55,018
What's wrong with her waist?

14
00:01:55,018 --> 00:01:59,162
Before I gave birth to Dayang, my waist was also 1.8 feet.

15
00:01:59,162 --> 00:02:00,580
Not now, though.

16
00:02:00,580 --> 00:02:02,626
Yours isn't worth mentioning either.

17
00:02:04,650 --> 00:02:06,560
- Good morning.
- Hello.

18
00:02:06,560 --> 00:02:08,300
Did you come yesterday?

19
00:02:08,300 --> 00:02:09,490
Yes.

20
00:02:09,490 --> 00:02:11,050
This is Aunty Baoping.

21
00:02:11,050 --> 00:02:12,658
I'm Aunty A'Gui.

22
00:02:12,658 --> 00:02:16,489
One-third of the homestead in this courtyard belongs to my family.

23
00:02:16,489 --> 00:02:19,490
So, I'm the landlady.

24
00:02:19,490 --> 00:02:22,180
I'm responsible for the cleanliness of this courtyard.

25
00:02:22,180 --> 00:02:23,700
What's your name?

26
00:02:23,700 --> 00:02:24,910
I'm Bai Manjun.

27
00:02:24,910 --> 00:02:27,290
Just call me Xiao Bai.

28
00:02:27,290 --> 00:02:28,530
Xiao Bai.

29
00:02:28,530 --> 00:02:30,566
What are you doing?

30
00:02:30,566 --> 00:02:31,910
I'm doing yoga.

31
00:02:31,910 --> 00:02:33,956
What's yoga?

32
00:02:33,956 --> 00:02:36,090
Perhaps it's the same as Mr. Ma's practices.

33
00:02:36,090 --> 00:02:38,050
Mr. Ma sat there motionlessly,

34
00:02:38,050 --> 00:02:40,420
but she's moving and doing handstands.

35
00:02:40,420 --> 00:02:41,330
Right?

36
00:02:41,330 --> 00:02:43,130
What?

37
00:02:43,130 --> 00:02:44,320
Keep going.

38
00:02:44,320 --> 00:02:46,200
Let's go upstairs.

39
00:02:50,030 --> 00:02:52,150
Why doesn't she feel dizzy?

40
00:02:52,150 --> 00:02:55,022
Youngsters don't get dizzy.

41
00:02:55,980 --> 00:02:57,750
Dried bamboo shoots

42
00:02:57,750 --> 00:02:59,550
and porcini.

43
00:02:59,550 --> 00:03:01,534
I dried all for these for you.

44
00:03:01,534 --> 00:03:02,610
Don't be afraid.

45
00:03:02,610 --> 00:03:04,860
These aren't toxic!

46
00:03:04,860 --> 00:03:07,096
I'm not afraid.

47
00:03:07,096 --> 00:03:09,200
Aunty A'Gui, I'm not!

48
00:03:09,200 --> 00:03:11,310
Well...This is too much.

49
00:03:11,310 --> 00:03:12,610
It's really too much.

50
00:03:12,610 --> 00:03:18,890
You need to bring back more for your parents to eat.

51
00:03:18,890 --> 00:03:21,580
These cow's milk cheese and sausages are from me.

52
00:03:21,580 --> 00:03:22,610
Thank you.

53
00:03:22,610 --> 00:03:25,110
This is from A'Feng.

54
00:03:25,110 --> 00:03:27,580
Dried peaches and apples.

55
00:03:27,580 --> 00:03:30,530
These are from their orchard.

56
00:03:30,530 --> 00:03:32,810
Very organic.

57
00:03:32,810 --> 00:03:34,560
The dried peaches are great.

58
00:03:34,560 --> 00:03:36,832
They taste sweet even when soaked in water.

59
00:03:36,832 --> 00:03:37,860
- Thank you.
- These, too.

60
00:03:37,860 --> 00:03:43,104
Granny Xiuying's chili and sesame.

61
00:03:43,104 --> 00:03:46,480
Granny Caiyun's black soybeans and soybeans.

62
00:03:47,140 --> 00:03:48,560
Where's Aunty E's fish?

63
00:03:48,560 --> 00:03:49,300
Where is it?

64
00:03:49,300 --> 00:03:50,700
Over here.

65
00:03:50,700 --> 00:03:52,350
Dried fish.

66
00:03:54,330 --> 00:03:57,310
How are you going to bring everything back?

67
00:03:57,310 --> 00:03:58,870
You've brought too much over! Goodness!

68
00:03:58,870 --> 00:04:03,670
Besides... I haven't given you any gifts or done anything for you.

69
00:04:03,670 --> 00:04:05,980
These are just tokens of our appreciation.

70
00:04:05,980 --> 00:04:08,580
You've been busy volunteering

71
00:04:08,580 --> 00:04:10,808
and helping A'Yao tons.

72
00:04:10,808 --> 00:04:12,580
All of us like you.

73
00:04:12,580 --> 00:04:17,352
The grannies and aunties in the village don't want you to leave.

74
00:04:17,352 --> 00:04:21,430
Hongdou, after you leave, don't forget us.

75
00:04:21,430 --> 00:04:24,634
Remember to visit us.

76
00:04:24,634 --> 00:04:27,460
Hongdou will be too busy to visit us.

77
00:04:27,460 --> 00:04:29,536
Just make a call.

78
00:04:29,536 --> 00:04:31,230
A video call!

79
00:04:31,230 --> 00:04:32,930
Yes.

80
00:04:37,530 --> 00:04:39,330
I've prepared some gifts.

81
00:04:39,330 --> 00:04:40,500
Some are unopened.

82
00:04:40,500 --> 00:04:43,040
All of these are for you.

83
00:04:44,270 --> 00:04:45,720
- Xiao Hu Lu.
- I'm here!

84
00:04:45,720 --> 00:04:46,830
- Tuotuo.
- I'm here!

85
00:04:46,830 --> 00:04:47,810
- Huzi.
- I'm here!

86
00:04:47,810 --> 00:04:49,260
- Guobao.
- I want one, too!

87
00:04:49,260 --> 00:04:50,530
You have to say, "Here"!

88
00:04:50,530 --> 00:04:51,410
Here!

89
00:04:51,410 --> 00:04:52,510
Here you go.

90
00:04:52,510 --> 00:04:53,620
This is for you.

91
00:04:53,620 --> 00:04:55,756
Thank you, Sister.

92
00:04:56,390 --> 00:04:57,290
Here you go.

93
00:04:57,290 --> 00:05:01,454
- Thank you, Sister.
- Thank you, Sister.

94
00:05:02,140 --> 00:05:04,244
Thank you, Sister.

95
00:05:05,190 --> 00:05:07,262
Hongdou, what's this?

96
00:05:07,262 --> 00:05:08,600
That's a Luban lock.

97
00:05:08,600 --> 00:05:11,528
A Luban lock?

98
00:05:11,528 --> 00:05:12,940
Make a promise to me.

99
00:05:12,940 --> 00:05:18,770
After I leave, accompany Granny Xie at A'Yao's home more often.

100
00:05:18,770 --> 00:05:20,480
- Okay?
- <i>Okay.</i>

101
00:05:20,480 --> 00:05:21,870
Does Granny know how to play games?

102
00:05:21,870 --> 00:05:22,700
You can teach her.

103
00:05:22,700 --> 00:05:24,400
Okay.

104
00:05:24,400 --> 00:05:28,830
Sister Hongdou, will you bring Lingdang here to visit me?

105
00:05:31,190 --> 00:05:32,140
I don't know.

106
00:05:32,140 --> 00:05:35,992
After you leave, who will marry Uncle A'Yao?

107
00:05:37,460 --> 00:05:38,620
I don't know either.

108
00:05:38,620 --> 00:05:41,330
When will there be a feast with stewed pork?

109
00:05:41,330 --> 00:05:42,680
I want to eat sugar rice!

110
00:05:42,680 --> 00:05:44,270
Me too!

111
00:05:44,270 --> 00:05:47,278
Forget it, they won't get married.

112
00:05:47,278 --> 00:05:49,870
We won't get to eat stewed pork.

113
00:05:49,870 --> 00:05:53,186
No sugar rice for us.

114
00:05:56,650 --> 00:06:04,240
One, two, three! One, two, three!

115
00:06:15,210 --> 00:06:18,460
It's out! Come on!

116
00:06:24,060 --> 00:06:26,720
All done. Thank you, buddy. Thank you.

117
00:06:26,720 --> 00:06:28,370
Brother Jiu! I have something else on. I'll get going.

118
00:06:28,370 --> 00:06:29,720
Okay. Thanks, A'Yao.

119
00:06:29,720 --> 00:06:30,610
- Not at all.
- I'm off. Bye-bye.

120
00:06:30,610 --> 00:06:31,730
Thank you!

121
00:06:31,730 --> 00:06:33,198
Thank you, brother.

122
00:06:33,198 --> 00:06:34,970
Thanks.

123
00:06:35,920 --> 00:06:37,820
Thank you.

124
00:06:38,830 --> 00:06:40,760
All done. Thank you.

125
00:06:51,560 --> 00:06:53,430
Didn't the tractor fall into the ditch?

126
00:06:53,430 --> 00:06:56,080
Yeah. I was covered in mud. So, I went home to take a bath.

127
00:06:56,080 --> 00:06:57,060
Luckily, I made it here in time.

128
00:06:57,060 --> 00:06:58,600
I already told you that I can go back on my own.

129
00:06:58,600 --> 00:07:01,352
I said I'd pick you up.

130
00:07:02,720 --> 00:07:03,900
Your wound is infected.

131
00:07:03,900 --> 00:07:05,630
Did bath water get onto it?

132
00:07:05,630 --> 00:07:07,571
I'm fine. It doesn't hurt.

133
00:07:07,571 --> 00:07:08,730
You have to be careful.

134
00:07:08,730 --> 00:07:10,590
Otherwise, it'll leave a scar.

135
00:07:10,590 --> 00:07:11,680
Got it.

136
00:07:11,680 --> 00:07:14,764
Should we take the seaside route?

137
00:07:14,764 --> 00:07:16,090
A detour?

138
00:07:16,090 --> 00:07:18,822
We can watch the sunset.

139
00:07:30,730 --> 00:07:32,630
Xie Zhiyao.

140
00:07:33,720 --> 00:07:36,080
Why are you taking photos of me?

141
00:07:36,080 --> 00:07:37,860
As a keepsake.

142
00:07:39,950 --> 00:07:42,298
You're behaving like a tourist now.

143
00:07:42,298 --> 00:07:44,492
I am a tourist.

144
00:07:44,492 --> 00:07:47,160
Fine. A tourist.

145
00:07:47,720 --> 00:07:52,000
Aunty Baoping and the rest are thinking about giving you food.

146
00:07:52,000 --> 00:07:56,178
After much thought, I still don't know what to give you.

147
00:07:56,950 --> 00:07:58,330
Are you joking?

148
00:07:58,330 --> 00:08:00,558
You've already given me tons of things.

149
00:08:00,558 --> 00:08:02,772
What did I give you?

150
00:08:05,000 --> 00:08:07,860
The sunrise. The sunset.

151
00:08:07,860 --> 00:08:09,570
The starry sky.

152
00:08:09,570 --> 00:08:11,320
The wind.

153
00:08:11,320 --> 00:08:14,790
Courage. Hope.

154
00:08:14,790 --> 00:08:17,350
Can't you be more materialistic?

155
00:08:20,460 --> 00:08:22,940
I think I'm richer than you.

156
00:08:23,630 --> 00:08:25,430
I have no loans.

157
00:08:49,520 --> 00:08:51,320
It's beautiful.

158
00:09:04,120 --> 00:09:07,529
You've really learned to enjoy the moment.

159
00:09:07,529 --> 00:09:09,578
Of course.

160
00:09:09,578 --> 00:09:12,570
These are the real luxuries.

161
00:09:32,570 --> 00:09:34,830
Why are you silent?

162
00:09:35,650 --> 00:09:39,214
I'm wondering how to express myself.

163
00:09:39,214 --> 00:09:41,210
Express what?

164
00:09:41,210 --> 00:09:43,400
Just speak your mind.

165
00:10:10,000 --> 00:10:11,800
It's a parting gift.

166
00:10:13,400 --> 00:10:15,300
I made it myself.

167
00:10:15,300 --> 00:10:17,000
It's not an expensive trinket.

168
00:10:17,000 --> 00:10:18,800
I reckon you'd refuse a pricey gift.

169
00:10:18,800 --> 00:10:20,300
You made it?

170
00:10:20,300 --> 00:10:21,800
What's wrong?

171
00:10:32,300 --> 00:10:34,600
Why are the two rings interlocked?

172
00:10:35,600 --> 00:10:36,700
Magic.

173
00:10:36,700 --> 00:10:39,000
Balala dark magic.

174
00:10:45,800 --> 00:10:47,900
You don't like it?

175
00:10:48,700 --> 00:10:50,100
I love it.

176
00:10:50,800 --> 00:10:52,300
Thank you.

177
00:10:57,800 --> 00:11:00,000
Did you injure your hand?

178
00:11:00,000 --> 00:11:02,800
Nah. It's red from pushing the tractor.

179
00:11:20,700 --> 00:11:23,300
Looks good, right? It does.

180
00:11:23,300 --> 00:11:26,200
You're pretty. So, everything you put on looks good.

181
00:11:49,500 --> 00:11:50,800
Xu Hongdou.

182
00:12:03,200 --> 00:12:05,600
When I first met you,

183
00:12:05,600 --> 00:12:08,600
I thought you were uptight and plain.

184
00:12:08,600 --> 00:12:13,200
After interacting with you, I realized you're an unlucky but interesting person.

185
00:12:13,200 --> 00:12:15,600
Every time I asked you for a favor,

186
00:12:15,600 --> 00:12:18,900
you'd seem unwilling but give in anyway.

187
00:12:19,800 --> 00:12:21,400
How should I put this?

188
00:12:21,400 --> 00:12:23,500
I think you're...

189
00:12:26,400 --> 00:12:28,300
I think you're someone...

190
00:12:29,800 --> 00:12:31,400
who's just right.

191
00:12:34,000 --> 00:12:35,800
Just right?

192
00:12:37,500 --> 00:12:41,600
Just right to captivate my heart.

193
00:12:45,400 --> 00:12:47,700
Every day that I'm with you,

194
00:12:47,700 --> 00:12:50,000
I'm overjoyed.

195
00:12:50,900 --> 00:12:54,800
I feel delighted whether we're occupied or not.

196
00:12:55,700 --> 00:12:57,200
So pleased that...

197
00:12:58,400 --> 00:12:59,900
I'm feeling down.

198
00:13:01,900 --> 00:13:05,400
That's because we met at a time and place that isn't that great.

199
00:13:07,800 --> 00:13:10,470
Sometimes, I even start to regret it.

200
00:13:11,200 --> 00:13:13,200
When I was in Beijing,

201
00:13:13,200 --> 00:13:16,000
I often passed the hotel where you worked at,

202
00:13:16,000 --> 00:13:18,100
but I never walked in.

203
00:13:19,320 --> 00:13:23,832
If I went in, I could've gotten to know you earlier.

204
00:13:24,840 --> 00:13:29,160
Maybe there would've been another possibility between us.

205
00:13:33,500 --> 00:13:37,500
I intended to let these words sink in my heart,

206
00:13:38,900 --> 00:13:40,800
but I gave this much thought.

207
00:13:42,400 --> 00:13:44,000
At the very end,

208
00:13:45,400 --> 00:13:47,600
I want to gift you another memory.

209
00:13:49,200 --> 00:13:52,200
By the seaside, where the wind blows...

210
00:13:53,000 --> 00:13:55,900
and the sunset glow is our witness,

211
00:13:57,000 --> 00:14:01,800
a man devoted his heart to you.

212
00:14:01,800 --> 00:14:10,000
♫ <i>I'll give you the saddle of my heart</i> ♫

213
00:14:11,600 --> 00:14:13,000
I spoke my mind.

214
00:14:14,200 --> 00:14:18,300
Xie Zhiyao, you sure are bold.

215
00:14:18,300 --> 00:14:19,400
Unexpected, right?

216
00:14:19,400 --> 00:14:21,000
I'm forthright.

217
00:14:22,400 --> 00:14:24,400
I don't know what to say.

218
00:14:24,400 --> 00:14:26,400
That's what I want.

219
00:14:30,200 --> 00:14:31,600
All right, come on.

220
00:14:31,600 --> 00:14:33,000
Why are you crying?

221
00:14:33,000 --> 00:14:35,000
You don't have to be so nice.

222
00:14:36,100 --> 00:14:43,400
♫ <i>I'm searching for a meadow of mine</i> ♫

223
00:14:45,400 --> 00:14:46,700
Thank you.

224
00:14:47,600 --> 00:14:49,600
I love this gift.

225
00:14:51,400 --> 00:14:55,000
You're welcome. Xu Hongdou,

226
00:14:56,100 --> 00:14:58,400
live the life you want.

227
00:14:59,200 --> 00:15:01,200
I wish you happiness.

228
00:15:04,000 --> 00:15:06,000
♫ <i>Would you ask for any horse</i> ♫

229
00:15:06,000 --> 00:15:07,400
Thank you.

230
00:15:07,400 --> 00:15:12,000
♫ <i>But this one inside your heart</i> ♫

231
00:15:12,000 --> 00:15:20,800
♫ <i>I'll give you the saddle of my heart</i> ♫

232
00:15:29,600 --> 00:15:31,400
Let's go back.

233
00:15:32,800 --> 00:15:36,000
♫ <i>A feeling rushes over me</i> ♫

234
00:15:36,000 --> 00:15:40,400
♫ <i>Spills my heart into the field</i> ♫

235
00:15:40,400 --> 00:15:47,200
♫ <i>I know it, I will be yours</i> ♫

236
00:15:47,200 --> 00:15:50,200
♫ <i>Would you ask for any horse</i> ♫

237
00:15:50,200 --> 00:15:51,800
♫ <i>But this one inside your heart</i> ♫

238
00:15:51,800 --> 00:15:54,600
Hongdou, have a safe trip.

239
00:15:54,600 --> 00:15:56,700
Update me about the bookstore.

240
00:15:56,700 --> 00:15:58,500
Of course. Let's keep in touch.

241
00:15:58,500 --> 00:16:00,200
- Let us know about any resources.
- Okay.

242
00:16:00,200 --> 00:16:02,600
I'll mail your belongings to you tonight.

243
00:16:02,600 --> 00:16:05,300
Send me nice food when you're home.

244
00:16:06,000 --> 00:16:07,700
Have a safe trip.

245
00:16:08,500 --> 00:16:12,800
Send a message in the chat when you reach your friend's home.

246
00:16:28,600 --> 00:16:30,400
Off you go.

247
00:16:47,000 --> 00:16:50,000
♫ <i>Do you ever feel alone</i> ♫

248
00:16:50,000 --> 00:16:52,600
♫ <i>Standing in the road</i> ♫

249
00:16:52,600 --> 00:16:56,000
♫ <i>Don't know where to go</i> ♫

250
00:16:57,500 --> 00:17:00,700
♫ <i>In the air, my memories flow</i> ♫

251
00:17:00,700 --> 00:17:03,400
♫ <i>Faces in a row</i> ♫

252
00:17:03,400 --> 00:17:07,000
♫ <i>Take a long way home</i> ♫

253
00:17:07,000 --> 00:17:14,000
♫ <i>But all of this reminds me to believe</i> ♫

254
00:17:14,000 --> 00:17:17,400
♫ <i>No one stays or leaves</i> ♫

255
00:17:17,400 --> 00:17:24,700
♫ <i>And all of this reminds me to receive</i> ♫

256
00:17:24,700 --> 00:17:28,800
♫ <i>The life we can see</i> ♫

257
00:17:34,000 --> 00:17:38,800
♫ <i>The sun will rise and fall</i> ♫

258
00:17:44,200 --> 00:17:49,200
♫ <i>It's just another day</i> ♫

259
00:18:14,230 --> 00:18:18,920
<i>[Domestic Departures]</i>

260
00:18:21,500 --> 00:18:23,200
Go on in.

261
00:18:23,200 --> 00:18:25,000
I'll see you off.

262
00:18:28,200 --> 00:18:29,700
Give me a hug.

263
00:18:32,800 --> 00:18:34,700
Forget it.

264
00:18:34,700 --> 00:18:36,400
Get going.

265
00:18:42,200 --> 00:18:44,100
I think that hug's needed.

266
00:18:45,800 --> 00:18:48,300
Make up your mind.

267
00:19:03,460 --> 00:19:07,900
♫ <i>The sun will rise and fall</i> ♫

268
00:19:14,000 --> 00:19:18,800
♫ <i>It's just another day</i> ♫

269
00:19:22,000 --> 00:19:23,600
Have a safe trip.

270
00:19:27,400 --> 00:19:30,500
- Goodbye.
- Goodbye.

