00:29:06,800 --> 00:29:08,300
You have to get the knack for this.

435
00:29:08,300 --> 00:29:11,000
Do it like me. Sway and move. Yes.

436
00:29:11,000 --> 00:29:13,300
Well done. And, go.

437
00:29:13,300 --> 00:29:16,600
Xiaomei, is she the daughter of your cousin or your sister?

438
00:29:16,600 --> 00:29:17,600
She's my goddaughter.

439
00:29:17,600 --> 00:29:19,600
She came to visit from Beijing.

440
00:29:19,600 --> 00:29:22,000
Goddaughter? She traveled all the way form Beijing?

441
00:29:22,000 --> 00:29:23,700
That's great.

442
00:29:23,700 --> 00:29:26,500
She often mails food and drinks to me.

443
00:29:26,500 --> 00:29:28,400
That's really nice.

444
00:29:32,900 --> 00:29:34,200
Aunty,

445
00:29:34,200 --> 00:29:37,600
Chen Nanxing told me that you took an entire night to give birth to her.

446
00:29:37,600 --> 00:29:39,600
When she was born the next morning,

447
00:29:39,600 --> 00:29:43,000
Uncle had just seen the South Star in the sky.

448
00:29:43,000 --> 00:29:44,900
So, she was named Chen Nanxing.

449
00:29:44,900 --> 00:29:46,400
I was duped by her for ages.

450
00:29:46,400 --> 00:29:48,500
A while back, I learned that

451
00:29:48,500 --> 00:29:51,770
the South Star can't be seen in the northern hemisphere.

452
00:29:55,900 --> 00:29:58,400
She was named by her grandfather.

453
00:29:58,400 --> 00:30:01,200
He grew arum lilies, Tian Nan Xing, in his yard.

454
00:30:01,200 --> 00:30:03,400
These didn't need much water to flourish.

455
00:30:03,400 --> 00:30:06,400
They were luxuriantly green, so he named her Nanxing.

456
00:30:06,400 --> 00:30:09,100
Yes. She hated her name when she was young.

457
00:30:09,100 --> 00:30:12,700
She detested sharing a name with the grass in her grandpa's yard.

458
00:30:16,200 --> 00:30:18,600
Let's get some apples.

