00:34:50,800 --> 00:34:53,600
I'm fine. There's enough. I'll scoop some for you.

538
00:35:17,300 --> 00:35:21,800
Are you crying because no one wants to eat your noodles?

539
00:35:21,800 --> 00:35:23,000
No.

540
00:35:25,320 --> 00:35:30,540
I just felt like it's been ages since I ate alone.

541
00:35:31,700 --> 00:35:33,500
Suddenly, I noticed

542
00:35:33,500 --> 00:35:35,300
the lights in all the rooms were off.

543
00:35:35,300 --> 00:35:36,700
So...

544
00:35:38,000 --> 00:35:42,000
So, I felt a little lonely.

545
00:35:42,800 --> 00:35:45,000
I'm just being sappy.

546
00:35:45,000 --> 00:35:46,800
I don't think so.

547
00:35:46,800 --> 00:35:50,400
You're just not used to the feeling of seperation.

548
00:35:52,400 --> 00:35:55,000
Look. I seem like a strong girl.

549
00:35:55,000 --> 00:35:56,700
When I visited my mom with my dad,

550
00:35:56,700 --> 00:36:01,200
I started bawling as soon as I left.

551
00:36:01,200 --> 00:36:02,800
Your mom must be really sad.

552
00:36:02,800 --> 00:36:05,700
No way. She was overjoyed to send me off.

553
00:36:05,700 --> 00:36:09,800
She has to cook for us when we're there. That's a disruption to her work.

554
00:36:09,800 --> 00:36:11,400
That can't be true.

555
00:36:11,400 --> 00:36:13,000
She's just acting aloof.

556
00:36:13,000 --> 00:36:14,000
It's true.

557
00:36:14,000 --> 00:36:17,000
My boyfriend secretly told me

558
00:36:17,000 --> 00:36:19,300
that my mom heaved a sigh of relief after we left.

559
00:36:19,300 --> 00:36:23,300
She even described my dad and me as clingy and unmovable statues.

560
00:36:24,400 --> 00:36:27,400
Your mom is my idol.

561
00:36:27,400 --> 00:36:29,600
Aren't I your idol?

562
00:36:29,600 --> 00:36:33,600
I've worshipped Principal Tao for ages.

563
00:36:33,600 --> 00:36:35,400
What about my fan club?

564
00:36:35,400 --> 00:36:37,500
It was quietly dissolved.

565
00:36:40,200 --> 00:36:41,900
Great.

566
00:36:41,900 --> 00:36:43,200
Sorry.

567
00:36:44,400 --> 00:36:47,400
Your conversation is so bleak.

568
00:36:47,400 --> 00:36:49,200
Yes, it's bleak.

569
00:36:49,200 --> 00:36:51,000
Everyone's gone.

570
00:36:53,500 --> 00:36:54,700
Don't worry.

571
00:36:54,700 --> 00:36:56,400
New tenants will come.

572
00:36:56,400 --> 00:36:59,000
The windows will be illuminated.

573
00:37:00,000 --> 00:37:01,500
It's not the same.

574
00:37:02,200 --> 00:37:04,100
No matter who comes,

575
00:37:04,800 --> 00:37:06,600
Damai and Hongdou...

576
00:37:08,000 --> 00:37:09,900
won't come.

577
00:37:21,100 --> 00:37:23,600
Don't cry.

578
00:37:23,600 --> 00:37:25,900
Old Xie, don't feel too upset either.

579
00:37:34,600 --> 00:37:36,000
Look.

580
00:37:58,800 --> 00:38:00,400
I'm just putting up a photo.

581
00:38:00,400 --> 00:38:02,200
Go to bed early.

582
00:38:02,200 --> 00:38:03,600
Aunty.

583
00:38:04,600 --> 00:38:05,800
Well,

584
00:38:09,400 --> 00:38:11,200
I'll be leaving tomorrow.

585
00:38:12,600 --> 00:38:13,800
Go to bed with me.

586
00:38:13,800 --> 00:38:16,000
Tell me more about Nan Nan.

587
00:38:28,000 --> 00:38:32,100
A friend told me

588
00:38:32,100 --> 00:38:35,200
when we talk about a person,

589
00:38:35,200 --> 00:38:37,000
they exist.

590
00:38:38,000 --> 00:38:40,500
When we stop talking about them,

591
00:38:44,100 --> 00:38:45,700
they disappear.

592
00:38:46,600 --> 00:38:49,200
Let's chat more about her.

593
00:39:03,600 --> 00:39:06,100
This was when Nan Nan was 100 days old.

594
00:39:07,200 --> 00:39:08,600
She's one year old here.

595
00:39:08,600 --> 00:39:10,800
Her grandma is carrying her.

596
00:39:13,400 --> 00:39:16,200
She was so plump back then.

597
00:39:16,200 --> 00:39:17,500
She has a large build.

598
00:39:17,500 --> 00:39:19,600
It took me two days to give birth to her.

599
00:39:19,600 --> 00:39:22,200
She weighed 3.9 kilograms when born.

600
00:39:22,200 --> 00:39:23,500
Her whole body was red.

601
00:39:23,500 --> 00:39:26,000
She was frowning and wailing.

602
00:39:26,000 --> 00:39:29,200
I took a look at her and got a shock.

603
00:39:29,200 --> 00:39:32,500
I wondered why I had such an ugly daughter.

604
00:39:37,900 --> 00:39:40,400
This was when she entered elementary school.

605
00:39:41,200 --> 00:39:43,600
Someone sold marinated chicken before her dad's company.

606
00:39:43,600 --> 00:39:45,800
Those large drumsticks.

607
00:39:45,800 --> 00:39:48,600
She ate one every day.

608
00:39:48,600 --> 00:39:52,200
Other kids were picky with food,

609
00:39:52,200 --> 00:39:54,100
but she wasn't.

610
00:39:54,100 --> 00:39:56,200
She ate anything served to her.

611
00:39:57,900 --> 00:39:59,800
She's thinner here.

612
00:39:59,800 --> 00:40:01,000
Yes.

613
00:40:03,200 --> 00:40:05,300
Uncle was so handsome back then.

614
00:40:06,600 --> 00:40:09,300
This is probably when she was in junior high.

615
00:40:09,300 --> 00:40:10,700
I think it was her grandma's birthday.

616
00:40:10,700 --> 00:40:12,500
There's a cake over here.

617
00:40:13,440 --> 00:40:17,856
She slimmed down because she ate less and wanted to be pretty.

618
00:40:21,000 --> 00:40:23,600
She was taller than me by this time.

619
00:40:30,300 --> 00:40:32,300
She resembles her dad.

620
00:40:32,300 --> 00:40:33,800
Right?

621
00:40:54,800 --> 00:40:57,500
When Nan Nan just passed away,

622
00:40:58,400 --> 00:41:01,200
